<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="wise-adj">wise <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'waɪz/    美 /'waɪz/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(人因阅历丰富而) 有智慧的；英明的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The older, the wiser.
越老越聪明。/姜是老的辣。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Life makes a wise man smile and a foolish man cry.
生活让智者微笑，让愚者哭泣。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-sensible">2.★ <strong>(行为、决定等) 高明的；明智的 (sensible)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>a wise move</strong> / choice / decision
明智之举/明智的选择/明智的决定</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If you are learning new worlds, <strong>it is wise to</strong> use small cards with the words written on them.
如果你学习的是新单词，使用写有这些单词的小卡片是明智之举。</p><footer>人教新必修①-Welcome Unit</footer></div></div>